00:12:06.319 --> 00:12:08.960
the Bible tells us this great truth

00:12:08.960 --> 00:12:12.479
with regard to not only the creative work of God

00:12:12.479 --> 00:12:13.839
that He is the Creator,

00:12:13.839 --> 00:12:16.279
but understanding that He upholds all things,

00:12:16.279 --> 00:12:19.119
that He is the sustainer of all things.

00:12:19.119 --> 00:12:20.919
The Bible says this in Hebrews 1

00:12:20.919 --> 00:12:22.080
and verse number 3,

00:12:22.080 --> 00:12:24.119
who being the brightness of His glory

00:12:24.119 --> 00:12:26.199
and the express image of His Person

00:12:26.199 --> 00:12:28.559
and upholding all things

00:12:28.559 --> 00:12:31.199
by the Word of His power,

00:12:31.199 --> 00:12:33.839
when He had by Himself purged our sins,

00:12:33.839 --> 00:12:36.639
sat down on the right hand of the Majesty on high,

00:12:36.639 --> 00:12:38.880
and what great truth is given to us

00:12:38.880 --> 00:12:40.080
in verse number 3,

00:12:40.080 --> 00:12:41.760
not only that of creation

00:12:41.760 --> 00:12:43.520
and the sustaining work of God,

00:12:43.520 --> 00:12:45.559
but that of redemption as well

00:12:45.559 --> 00:12:47.919
is given to us at the end of verse number 3.

00:12:47.919 --> 00:12:49.919
But we find that He is the sustainer.

00:12:49.919 --> 00:12:51.919
Why is it that we have the laws

00:12:51.919 --> 00:12:53.639
that we have in nature?

00:12:53.760 --> 00:12:57.119
It's because our God sustains all things.

00:12:57.119 --> 00:12:58.800
Without Him, you remove Him

00:12:58.800 --> 00:13:00.279
and it falls apart,

00:13:00.279 --> 00:13:03.639
but you find that He upholds all things

00:13:03.639 --> 00:13:07.400
by the Word of His power.

00:13:07.400 --> 00:13:10.160
Phenomenal.

00:13:10.160 --> 00:13:12.080
He's precious.

00:13:12.080 --> 00:13:13.360
He's Alpha and Omega.

00:13:13.360 --> 00:13:14.199
He's Almighty.

00:13:14.199 --> 00:13:15.720
He's Creator.

00:13:15.720 --> 00:13:16.839
He is the sustainer.

00:13:16.839 --> 00:13:18.880
Notice He is compassionate.

00:13:18.880 --> 00:13:20.600
I love the fact that you find

00:13:20.600 --> 00:13:22.320
throughout the Word of God

00:13:22.360 --> 00:13:23.440
and in Matthew 9,

00:13:23.440 --> 00:13:25.680
we'll look there at this portion of Scripture,

00:13:25.680 --> 00:13:28.880
but you find the compassion of Christ.

00:13:28.880 --> 00:13:32.160
You find that our God is compassionate.

00:13:32.160 --> 00:13:33.960
And here in Matthew 9,

00:13:33.960 --> 00:13:36.760
the Bible tells us that there was a multitude

00:13:36.760 --> 00:13:38.479
and Jesus saw the multitudes

00:13:38.479 --> 00:13:39.919
in verse number 36

00:13:39.919 --> 00:13:42.080
and it tells us that He was moved

00:13:42.080 --> 00:13:43.600
with compassion on them.

00:13:43.600 --> 00:13:45.040
Why?

00:13:45.040 --> 00:13:47.119
Because they fainted and were scattered abroad

00:13:47.119 --> 00:13:50.919
as sheep having no shepherd.

00:13:50.960 --> 00:13:54.360
He was moved with compassion.

00:13:54.360 --> 00:13:55.479
We mentioned this morning

00:13:55.479 --> 00:13:56.680
in our Sunday school hours,

00:13:56.680 --> 00:13:58.520
we're studying the miracles of Christ

00:13:58.520 --> 00:14:00.080
that we were able to witness

00:14:00.080 --> 00:14:02.119
the compassion of Christ

00:14:02.119 --> 00:14:04.119
and the power of Christ.

00:14:04.119 --> 00:14:07.160
I'm thankful here that as you note here

00:14:07.160 --> 00:14:09.000
that He's moved with compassion,

00:14:09.000 --> 00:14:10.360
you find this referenced

00:14:10.360 --> 00:14:12.720
in other portions of Scripture as well

00:14:12.720 --> 00:14:15.040
that He is compassionate.

00:14:15.040 --> 00:14:17.519
He is gracious.

00:14:17.519 --> 00:14:20.799
Faith sang about God's grace this morning.

00:14:20.839 --> 00:14:22.640
We understand that many of us,

00:14:22.640 --> 00:14:24.920
even as we sang at the conclusion of our service

00:14:24.920 --> 00:14:26.080
last Sunday morning,

00:14:26.080 --> 00:14:27.119
amazing grace,

00:14:27.119 --> 00:14:29.760
that we are very thankful for the grace of God.

00:14:29.760 --> 00:14:32.519
In our text of Scripture in 1 Peter 2,

00:14:32.519 --> 00:14:34.200
in verse number 3,

00:14:34.200 --> 00:14:35.839
we read it just a moment ago,

00:14:35.839 --> 00:14:37.880
and the Bible says this

00:14:37.880 --> 00:14:39.760
with regard to the grace of God,

00:14:39.760 --> 00:14:42.040
if so be that ye have tasted

00:14:42.040 --> 00:14:46.239
that the Lord is gracious.

00:14:46.239 --> 00:14:47.360
It's part of His nature.

00:14:47.360 --> 00:14:48.679
It's who He is.

00:14:48.679 --> 00:14:51.600
He's gracious.

00:14:51.600 --> 00:14:54.000
And you think about the grace of God.

00:14:54.000 --> 00:14:55.920
His saving grace.

00:14:55.920 --> 00:14:57.200
His serving grace.

00:14:57.200 --> 00:14:59.839
And you find that we sing about His amazing grace.

00:14:59.839 --> 00:15:01.880
Paul speaks about His abundant grace.

00:15:01.880 --> 00:15:04.000
And you find that as we understand

00:15:04.000 --> 00:15:05.279
the grace of God,

00:15:05.279 --> 00:15:06.799
and we understand this morning

00:15:06.799 --> 00:15:11.080
that we have been the recipients of His grace.

00:15:11.080 --> 00:15:14.160
For by grace are you saved through faith.

00:15:14.160 --> 00:15:15.480
And that not of yourselves,

00:15:15.480 --> 00:15:16.839
it is the gift of God,

00:15:16.839 --> 00:15:17.679
but not of works,

00:15:17.679 --> 00:15:19.880
lest any man should boast.

00:15:19.880 --> 00:15:22.480
Oh, the grace of God.

00:15:22.480 --> 00:15:25.480
How precious our God is.

00:15:25.480 --> 00:15:27.600
He's merciful.

00:15:27.600 --> 00:15:30.239
Grace and mercy are often used together.

00:15:30.239 --> 00:15:31.679
And we find that when you speak

00:15:31.679 --> 00:15:34.360
of these two attributes of our God,

00:15:34.360 --> 00:15:36.040
that yes, indeed, they are similar,

00:15:36.040 --> 00:15:38.600
yet there are contrasts between the two.

00:15:38.600 --> 00:15:41.119
God giving us what we do not deserve

00:15:41.119 --> 00:15:42.640
in one aspect,

00:15:42.640 --> 00:15:44.080
and then God not giving us

00:15:44.080 --> 00:15:46.279
what we do deserve.

00:15:46.720 --> 00:15:50.119
Turn over to Ephesians 2.

00:15:50.119 --> 00:15:53.679
The reality is that we deserve punishment.

00:15:53.679 --> 00:15:55.959
Listen, we are guilty.

00:15:55.959 --> 00:15:56.880
Amen?

00:15:56.880 --> 00:15:58.720
We're sinners. We're guilty.

00:15:58.720 --> 00:16:00.799
The reality is that Paul begins

00:16:00.799 --> 00:16:02.480
this great passage of Scripture

00:16:02.480 --> 00:16:04.480
by speaking about those that were saved,

00:16:04.480 --> 00:16:08.119
but he reminds them of their past.

00:16:08.119 --> 00:16:10.000
In Ephesians 2 and verse 1,

00:16:10.000 --> 00:16:12.600
"...and you hath He quickened

00:16:12.600 --> 00:16:15.080
who were dead in trespasses and sins."

00:16:15.119 --> 00:16:17.119
By the way, we were dead

00:16:17.119 --> 00:16:20.600
in our trespasses and sins.

00:16:20.600 --> 00:16:21.880
"...you hath He quickened."

00:16:21.880 --> 00:16:23.519
If you've been born again this morning,

00:16:23.519 --> 00:16:25.119
if you've trusted Jesus Christ

00:16:25.119 --> 00:16:27.000
as your personal Savior this morning,

00:16:27.000 --> 00:16:29.760
you've been made alive.

00:16:29.760 --> 00:16:34.279
You were dead spiritually.

00:16:34.279 --> 00:16:35.119
He says this,

00:16:35.119 --> 00:16:37.600
"...wherein in time past

00:16:37.600 --> 00:16:40.360
ye walked according to the course of this world.

00:16:40.360 --> 00:16:42.480
According to the Prince of the power of the air,

00:16:42.480 --> 00:16:43.720
the Spirit that now worketh

00:16:43.720 --> 00:16:45.559
on the children of disobedience,

00:16:45.559 --> 00:16:48.440
among whom also we all had our conversation

00:16:48.440 --> 00:16:51.440
in times past in the lust of our flesh."

00:16:51.440 --> 00:16:54.080
Can we identify with what's being said?

00:16:54.080 --> 00:16:55.559
There was a time in your life

00:16:55.559 --> 00:16:57.600
that you were not saved.

00:16:57.600 --> 00:16:59.880
And that time in your life when you were not saved

00:16:59.880 --> 00:17:02.360
is described here that we all

00:17:02.360 --> 00:17:05.040
were in this same condition in time past.

00:17:05.040 --> 00:17:09.320
We're following the lust of our flesh.

00:17:09.320 --> 00:17:11.239
"...fulfilling the desires of the flesh

00:17:11.239 --> 00:17:12.320
and of the mind,

00:17:12.360 --> 00:17:14.279
for we're by nature the children of wrath

00:17:14.279 --> 00:17:18.559
even as others."

00:17:18.559 --> 00:17:20.959
But God.

00:17:20.959 --> 00:17:22.600
But God.

00:17:22.600 --> 00:17:27.760
"...who is rich in mercy

00:17:27.760 --> 00:17:29.760
for His great love

00:17:29.760 --> 00:17:31.760
wherewith He loved us."

00:17:31.760 --> 00:17:34.320
Aren't you thankful for the mercy of God?

00:17:34.320 --> 00:17:35.559
He's merciful.

00:17:35.559 --> 00:17:36.600
Who He is.

00:17:36.600 --> 00:17:38.320
As we look at these,

00:17:38.320 --> 00:17:41.440
just a list of things that I've put together

00:17:41.480 --> 00:17:43.200
to encourage my heart,

00:17:43.200 --> 00:17:45.320
to trust that it would be an encouragement

00:17:45.320 --> 00:17:46.519
to your heart as well,

00:17:46.519 --> 00:17:48.080
that we're mindful this morning,

00:17:48.080 --> 00:17:49.600
we're thankful for His Person,

00:17:49.600 --> 00:17:51.559
for who He is.

00:17:51.559 --> 00:17:53.880
Yes, that I'm a recipient of His grace,

00:17:53.880 --> 00:17:55.959
and yes, that I'm a recipient of His mercy,

00:17:55.959 --> 00:17:57.320
but why am I a recipient?

00:17:57.320 --> 00:17:58.559
Because that's what He is.

00:17:58.559 --> 00:18:00.119
That's who He is.

00:18:00.119 --> 00:18:02.119
It's part of His very nature.

00:18:02.119 --> 00:18:03.679
He's gracious.

00:18:03.679 --> 00:18:05.480
And He's merciful.

00:18:05.480 --> 00:18:07.760
We find that He's long-suffering.

00:18:07.760 --> 00:18:11.200
Aren't you thankful that our God is long-suffering?

00:18:11.200 --> 00:18:12.760
Often times in our lives,

00:18:12.760 --> 00:18:15.480
we enjoy the long-suffering of God.

00:18:15.480 --> 00:18:17.600
2 Peter 3.

00:18:17.600 --> 00:18:19.040
There are times, however,

00:18:19.040 --> 00:18:21.000
when others perhaps may be enjoying

00:18:21.000 --> 00:18:22.440
the long-suffering of God

00:18:22.440 --> 00:18:24.040
that we don't seem to understand

00:18:24.040 --> 00:18:27.239
why God isn't dealing with them.

00:18:27.239 --> 00:18:29.440
But when God's being long-suffering to us,

00:18:29.440 --> 00:18:33.880
oh, we're so grateful for His long-suffering.

00:18:33.880 --> 00:18:37.080
I've often said over the years

00:18:37.080 --> 00:18:41.039
that we ought never mistake

00:18:41.039 --> 00:18:44.039
the long-suffering of God for His permission.

00:18:44.039 --> 00:18:47.080
God's never okay with sin. Never.

00:18:47.080 --> 00:18:49.799
But God is long-suffering to us.

00:18:49.799 --> 00:18:52.359
He's patient with us.

00:18:52.359 --> 00:18:54.320
And you begin to think here,

00:18:54.320 --> 00:18:57.200
the Bible within the context of 2 Peter 3

00:18:57.200 --> 00:18:59.559
is speaking of His promise

00:18:59.559 --> 00:19:00.880
with regard to His coming,

00:19:00.880 --> 00:19:01.479
but it says,

00:19:01.479 --> 00:19:03.520
"...the Lord is not slack concerning His promise,

00:19:03.520 --> 00:19:05.440
as some men cannot slacken His notice,

00:19:05.440 --> 00:19:08.280
but is long-suffering to us-ward,

00:19:08.280 --> 00:19:09.760
not willing that any should perish,

00:19:09.799 --> 00:19:12.520
but that all should come to repentance."

00:19:12.520 --> 00:19:15.239
I'm thankful that God is long-suffering.

00:19:15.239 --> 00:19:17.080
We sing a song with the children

00:19:17.080 --> 00:19:19.880
about God created all things.

00:19:19.880 --> 00:19:22.200
And He created all things in just six days.

00:19:22.200 --> 00:19:25.919
You go through all of the various aspects of creation,

00:19:25.919 --> 00:19:27.359
but then the song deals with,

00:19:27.359 --> 00:19:30.599
but He's still working on me.

00:19:30.599 --> 00:19:32.799
And He is! He's still working on us.

00:19:32.799 --> 00:19:35.760
He's long-suffering to us-ward.

00:19:35.760 --> 00:19:37.159
He's patient with us.

00:19:37.159 --> 00:19:38.840
By the way, aren't you thankful

00:19:38.880 --> 00:19:41.479
that He is long-suffering?

00:19:41.479 --> 00:19:44.000
He's not becoming any of these things.

00:19:44.000 --> 00:19:47.200
He is all of these things.

00:19:47.200 --> 00:19:49.080
He is precious.

00:19:49.080 --> 00:19:51.640
He's long-suffering to us.

00:19:51.640 --> 00:19:53.919
I believe, as I mentioned earlier,

00:19:53.919 --> 00:19:56.280
as I gave you the definition of precious

00:19:56.280 --> 00:19:59.440
and spoke about the office or rank

00:19:59.440 --> 00:20:00.440
that one holds.

00:20:00.440 --> 00:20:04.480
I've made this statement that He is King of kings

00:20:04.480 --> 00:20:07.060
and Lord of lords.

00:20:07.060 --> 00:20:09.500
The Bible tells us in Psalm 2,

00:20:09.500 --> 00:20:11.500
if you turn back over there just for a moment

00:20:11.500 --> 00:20:14.680
in how prophetic this particular portion of Scripture is

00:20:14.680 --> 00:20:17.040
even for the day in which we're living.

00:20:17.040 --> 00:20:21.840
In Psalm 2,

00:20:21.840 --> 00:20:24.040
the Bible speaks here with regard

00:20:24.040 --> 00:20:27.480
to the kings of the earth.

00:20:27.480 --> 00:20:29.560
In Psalm 2, in verse 1, it says,

00:20:29.560 --> 00:20:31.200
why do the heathen rage

00:20:31.200 --> 00:20:35.440
and the people imagine a vain thing?

00:20:35.440 --> 00:20:37.880
The kings of the earth set themselves

00:20:37.880 --> 00:20:40.600
and the rulers take counsel together

00:20:40.600 --> 00:20:42.120
against who?

00:20:42.120 --> 00:20:44.760
Against the Lord!

00:20:44.760 --> 00:20:46.520
And against His anointed saying,

00:20:46.520 --> 00:20:48.800
let us break their bands asunder

00:20:48.800 --> 00:20:51.560
and cast away their cords from us.

00:20:51.560 --> 00:20:53.280
Listen, we're living in a time

00:20:53.280 --> 00:20:55.600
where there's so much prophetic nature

00:20:55.600 --> 00:20:58.120
of this particular portion of Scripture.

00:20:58.200 --> 00:21:00.680
The kings of the earth set themselves,

00:21:00.680 --> 00:21:03.120
the rulers take counsel together

00:21:03.120 --> 00:21:05.720
against the Lord and against His anointed,

00:21:05.720 --> 00:21:07.560
but He, verse 4,

00:21:07.560 --> 00:21:12.560
that sitteth in the heavens shall laugh.

00:21:13.560 --> 00:21:17.480
The Lord shall have them in derision.

00:21:17.480 --> 00:21:18.520
Why does He laugh?

00:21:18.520 --> 00:21:21.440
Because He's King of kings and Lord of lords.

00:21:21.440 --> 00:21:23.360
No one's ever going to conquer Him.

00:21:23.360 --> 00:21:24.639
No one's going to defeat Him.

00:21:24.639 --> 00:21:26.720
No one's going to alter His plan.

00:21:26.760 --> 00:21:28.400
His plan will be fulfilled

00:21:28.400 --> 00:21:31.120
exactly as He has told us it will be fulfilled.

00:21:31.120 --> 00:21:33.080
He is King of kings, Lord of lords,

00:21:33.080 --> 00:21:35.720
the only potentate.

00:21:35.720 --> 00:21:37.040
We find that there are men,

00:21:37.040 --> 00:21:38.639
there are people upon this earth

00:21:38.639 --> 00:21:41.080
that have titles and have positions

00:21:41.080 --> 00:21:44.000
and we find that the Bible says in Proverbs

00:21:44.000 --> 00:21:46.080
that the heart of the king is where?

00:21:46.080 --> 00:21:48.520
It's in the hand of the Lord.

00:21:48.520 --> 00:21:51.420
And He turns it however He desires

00:21:51.420 --> 00:21:53.800
because He is King of kings and Lord of lords.

00:21:53.800 --> 00:21:55.600
All the kings of the earth,

00:21:55.600 --> 00:21:57.959
they can set themselves against the Lord

00:21:57.959 --> 00:21:59.639
and they can come up with their plans

00:21:59.639 --> 00:22:02.080
and they can devise all that they want to devise,

00:22:02.080 --> 00:22:05.020
but He is not in their hand.

00:22:05.020 --> 00:22:05.860
Amen?

00:22:05.860 --> 00:22:08.319
Listen, we ought to be thankful for that this morning.

00:22:08.319 --> 00:22:10.440
We ought to be thankful that He is King of kings

00:22:10.440 --> 00:22:11.800
and Lord of lords,

00:22:11.800 --> 00:22:14.400
that He is the great I Am.

00:22:14.400 --> 00:22:17.199
Let me say this, He is victorious.

00:22:19.199 --> 00:22:20.600
He never loses.

00:22:21.880 --> 00:22:23.199
Never.

00:22:23.199 --> 00:22:25.279
He is victorious.

00:22:25.279 --> 00:22:27.760
Satan thought he defeated Him, did he not?

00:22:29.839 --> 00:22:32.000
Pilate and all the Romans, the Jews,

00:22:32.000 --> 00:22:35.320
gave all the instruction with making that grave

00:22:35.320 --> 00:22:38.520
as sure, as secure as they could.

00:22:38.520 --> 00:22:41.440
Didn't matter what they did at that grave.

00:22:41.440 --> 00:22:43.760
As we sing on Easter morn,

00:22:43.760 --> 00:22:46.960
up from the grave He arose.

00:22:46.960 --> 00:22:47.800
Amen?

00:22:47.800 --> 00:22:48.680
He is victorious.

00:22:48.680 --> 00:22:50.520
Notice back in the Old Testament, if you will,

00:22:50.520 --> 00:22:52.360
1 Chronicles 29,

00:22:52.360 --> 00:22:55.440
I love the way that this particular portion of Scripture

00:22:55.440 --> 00:22:57.559
is the wording here.

00:22:57.559 --> 00:23:00.559
And what a joy when you think about the greatness

00:23:00.559 --> 00:23:01.820
and the power of our God.

00:23:01.820 --> 00:23:05.360
And in 1 Chronicles 29, in verse number 11,

00:23:05.360 --> 00:23:07.760
just a powerful verse of Scripture,

00:23:07.760 --> 00:23:10.600
perhaps a verse that you'd like to commit to memory

00:23:10.600 --> 00:23:14.040
and to be encouraged by the truth contained therein.

00:23:14.040 --> 00:23:18.600
The Bible says in 1 Chronicles 29, in verse number 11,

00:23:18.600 --> 00:23:22.919
Thine, O Lord, is the greatness and the power

00:23:22.919 --> 00:23:27.040
and the glory and the victory and the majesty

00:23:27.040 --> 00:23:31.919
for all that is in the heaven and in the earth is Thine.

00:23:31.919 --> 00:23:34.320
Thine is the kingdom, O Lord,

00:23:34.320 --> 00:23:39.320
and Thou art exalted as head above all.

00:23:39.800 --> 00:23:42.040
Isn't that a powerful verse of Scripture?

00:23:43.919 --> 00:23:46.119
I mean, you ought to memorize that verse of Scripture.

00:23:46.119 --> 00:23:47.160
Seriously.

00:23:48.160 --> 00:23:51.320
You see what, as David is worshiping,

00:23:51.320 --> 00:23:53.880
as David is giving the offering

00:23:53.880 --> 00:23:55.400
and as they're worshiping here,

00:23:55.400 --> 00:23:58.760
he gives us under the inspiration of the Holy Spirit of God

